The paper discusses a novel approach to tackling low-level errors in C, which is a software engineering problem (cs.SE). The approach involves implementing an introspection interface, which is a programming language concept (cs.PL). The paper also discusses the use of dynamic tools to maintain run-time information, which is a computer security issue (cs.CR) and a systems issue (cs.SY). Finally, the paper mentions the implementation of a more robust version of the C standard library, which involves machine learning techniques (cs.LG).
